text.tspan: How xclipboard works when another application owns the clipboard
xclipboard requests X clipboard for current clip content in target format
X clipboard calls Convertor Procedure of Application 1 for data in target format
Application 1 Convertor Procedure converts the selected data in target format
Convertor Procedure returns the data in target format
X clipboard returns the above data to xclipboard
Loser Procedure calls XtOwnSelection to take ownership of the clipboard
How Paste is done in X
Owner make a ConvertSelection request to X with target atom
X sends a SelectionRequestEvent to the owner
Owner Convertor Procedure converts the selected data in target format
Owner sends SelectionNotifyEvent to the requestor
X sends SelectionNotifyEvent to the the requestor if the clipboard is unowned
How Copy is done in X
Note: The owner matches the owner_window with the window
returned in Step 2. If both are not same, then Step 1 is failed
